{"title_page": "Bad Boy (Red Velvet song)", "text_new": "{{short description|Song by Red Velvet}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bad Boy\n| cover      = Redvelvetbadboy.png\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Taiwan physical cover\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]\n| album      = [[Perfect Velvet|The Perfect Red Velvet]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|1|29}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   = 2018\n| studio     = SM Studios, Seoul, South Korea\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Pop music|Trap]], [[R&B]]}}\n| length     = 3:31\n| label      = [[SM Entertainment]]\n| language   = [[Korean language|Korean]]|\n| writer     = {{hlist|JQ|Moon Hee-yeon}}<ref>[https://www.discogs.com/Red-Velvet-The-Perfect-Red-Velvet/release/12912383  The Perfect Red Velvet:Bad Boy] discogs</ref>\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[The Stereotypes]]|Maxx Song|Whitney Phillips|Yoo Young-jin}}\n| chronology = [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]] singles\n| prev_title = [[Peek-a-Boo (Red Velvet song)|Peek-a-Boo]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = #Cookie Jar\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|J_CFBjAyPWE|\"Bad Boy\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Bad Boy'''\" is a song by South Korean girl group [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]], released as a single from ''The Perfect Red Velvet'', the reissue of  ''[[Perfect Velvet]]'' (2017). It was released by [[S.M. Entertainment]] on January 29, 2018, along with the album and an accompanying music video. Written by S.M. Entertainment artist and songwriter [[Yoo Young-jin]] and produced by [[The Stereotypes]], Eazy, Maxx Song and Whitney Philips, \"Bad Boy\" is primarily an [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] song with elements of [[hip hop]] that has a synth melody and heavy bass sound. Its lyrics describe a relationship between the titular \"bad boy\" and a cold woman.\n\nThe song was well-received by critics overseas and in the group's native country South Korea, who praised the music, the music video and its choreography, and the group's transition to a sexy concept, something they have never attempted before. \"Bad Boy\" was included in ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard's]]'' '100 Best Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks' list, and topped their annual '20 Best K-pop Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks' list, they were the first female act to top this list. ''[[Dazed (magazine)|Dazed]]'' also included the song in their '20 best K-pop songs of 2018'. Commercially, the song was a domestic and international success, topping the Gaon Download Chart and charting at number two on the [[Gaon Digital Chart]] in South Korea. It charted at number two on ''Billboard's'' [[World Digital Songs]] chart. As of February 2020, it has sold over 500,000 units in the United States, has 250 million views on YouTube and 100 million streams on Spotify. The group entered the [[Canadian Hot 100]] for the first time with the song, making them only the seventh K-pop artist and the third female act to appear on the chart. It also charted in [[Japan]], [[Malaysia]] and [[Singapore]].\n\nThe song is also notable for being one of two songs (the other being \"[[Red Flavor]]\") performed by Red Velvet at the \"[[Spring is Coming]]\" concert in [[Pyongyang]] at the [[East Pyongyang Grand Theatre]] to an audience that included [[Kim Jong-un]]. The concert was seen as an act of [[cultural diplomacy]] and intended as part of a wider diplomatic initiative between South Korea and [[North Korea]]. Their appearance at the concert made them only the fifth idol group to ever perform in North Korea and the first artist from SM Entertainment in fifteen years since [[Shinhwa]].\n\n== Background ==\nA few months after the release of the group's second studio album ''[[Perfect Velvet]]'', the group's company [[S.M. Entertainment]] announced through an image teaser posted on their official [[social media]] accounts on January 23, 2018 that Red Velvet will be releasing their first reissue of an album, a repackage of ''Perfect Velvet'' titled ''The Perfect Red Velvet''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.mbn.co.kr/view.php?sc=71600002&year=2018&no=52708 |accessdate=January 24, 2018 |website=star.mbn|date=January 24, 2018 |script-title=ko:\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, \ud32c\ub4e4\uc5d0 \ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0? \"1\uc6d4 29\uc77c \ucee4\ubc0d \uc21c\"|language=korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.hankooki.com/lpage/entv/201801/sp20180124003258136730.htm |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Sports Hanguk|date=January 24, 2018 |script-title=ko:\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, \uc624\ub294 29\uc77c 'V\uc571' \uc0dd\ubc29\uc1a1 \uc9c4\ud589...Fan Card \ud1b5\ud55c \uc774\ubca4\ud2b8\uae4c\uc9c0 '\ud6c4\ub048'|language=korean}}</ref> The lead single was described as a song with a \"sexy\" or \"girl crush\" concept by South Korean news sites, which the group has never done before.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hei.hankyung.com/news/app/newsview.php?aid=201801241318H |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Hankyung|date=January 24, 2018 |script-title=ko:\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, '\ubc30\ub4dc \ubcf4\uc774'\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31\u2026\ube68\uac04\ub9db\u00b7\ud53c\uce74\ubd80 \uc774\uc740 \ud788\ud2b8 \uc608\uace0 |language=korean}}</ref>\n\nOn January 26, teaser images of members [[Wendy (singer)|Wendy]] and [[Joy (singer)|Joy]] were released through Red Velvet's social media accounts which Kang Seo-jung of ''Osen'' commented had the vibe of a powerful \"[[Korean honorifics#Honorific nouns|eonni]]\". Kang also noted how the song's concept differs from the group's past releases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110823236 |last=Kang |first=Seo-jung |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Osen|date=January 28, 2018 |script-title=ko:'\ucef4\ubc31' \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3\uc758 \uc644\ubcbd\ud55c '\ubc18\uc804'..\uc139\uc2dc \uac78\ud06c\ub7ec\uc2dc[\uc885\ud569] |language=korean}}</ref>\n\n== Composition ==\n{{Listen|filename=Bad Boy, Red Velvet song.ogg|title=\"Bad Boy\"|format=[[Ogg]]|pos=right|description=\"Bad Boy\" is an [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] song with elements of [[Hip hop music|hip hop]].}}\"Bad Boy\" is described as a [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]-based [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] song with a synth melody and a heavy bass sound.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insight.co.kr/news/136952 |last=Kim |first=Han-sol |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Insight |date=January 25, 2018 |script-title=ko:\ud30c\uaca9\uc801\uc778 '\uc139\uc2dc \ucee8\uc149'\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0\ud55c \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 '\ubc30\ub4dc\ubcf4\uc774' \ud2f0\uc800 \ucd5c\ucd08 \uacf5\uac1c |language=korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.kbs.co.kr/news/view.do?ncd=3597880 |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=KBS News|date=January 24, 2018 |script-title=ko:\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, \ub9ac\ud328\ud0a4\uc9c0 \uc568\ubc94\uc73c\ub85c 29\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1 '\ubc30\ub4dc \ubcf4\uc774' |language=korean}}</ref> The song was composed by Maxx Song , [[The Stereotypes]], Whitney Philips  and [[Yoo Young-jin]] with Korean lyrics by JQ ,Moon Hee-yeon<ref>[https://www.discogs.com/Red-Velvet-The-Perfect-Red-Velvet/release/12912383  The Perfect Red Velvet:Bad Boy] discogs</ref>  detailing the attraction and emotions between a 'bad boy' and a cold woman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110820387 |first=So-dam |last=Lee |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Osen|date=January 24, 2018|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] SM \"\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, 29\uc77c \ub9ac\ud328\ud0a4\uc9c0 \ubc1c\ub9e4..\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1\uc740 \ud799\ud569\" |language=korean}}</ref> Mexican news site ''[[Milenio]]'' called the song's melody a mix of R&B and hip hop and stated that its lyrics tell the story of the beginning of the couple's relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.milenio.com/hey/musica/bad-boy-grupo-kpop-red-velvet-encabeza-listas-musicales_0_1112889005.html|title='Bad Boy' del grupo de K-pop Red Velvet, encabeza listas musicales|website=Milenio|date=December 19, 2018|accessdate=February 16, 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref> On August 6, 2018 an English version of \"Bad Boy\" was released as a bonus track of their next EP \"[[Summer Magic (EP)|Summer Magic]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8467542/red-velvet-summer-magic-power-up-bad-boy-english-version |title=Red Velvet's 'Summer Magic' Features Lead Single 'Power Up' & English-Language Version of 'Bad Boy': Exclusive |first=Tamar |last=Herman |website=Billboard|date=July 29, 2018|accessdate=December 19, 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Music video and promotion==\nAn accompanying music video directed by Kim Ja-kyoung of Flexible Pictures and choreographed by Japanese [[hip hop]] dancer and choreographer Rie Hata, who had previously worked with [[CL (singer)|CL]] for the choreography of \"[[The Baddest Female (song)|The Baddest Female]]\" and with the group's label mate [[BoA]] for her single \"Nega Dola\", was released on the same day as the album and song.<ref>{{cite AV media notes| title=The Perfect Red Velvet| others=Red Velvet| publisher=[[S.M. Entertainment]]| language=ko| year=2018| type=booklet}}</ref> The video was called 'sultry' by Annie Martin of ''UPI'' and it featured the members in various coordinating outfits, which included all-black ensembles and pink pajamas. They were also seen in sexy uniforms, with athleisure fishnet-and-leather outfits. Tamar Herman of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' stated that it depicted the group as \"[[femme fatale]]s aiming to destroy the titular 'Bad Boy'\". She also noted how it wasn't \"particularly plot-oriented\" but \"the dangerous vibes of [[Irene (singer)|Irene]], [[Kang Seul-gi|Seulgi]], [[Wendy (singer)|Wendy]] and [[Joy (singer)|Joy]] contrast with the more youthful, unicorn-riding image of youngest-member [[Yeri (singer)|Yeri]], who the others seemingly protect, with Seulgi even covering her ears during one scene\". Talking about the choreography, she said that it was \"filled with suggestive hip rolls and aggressive come-hither hand motions, beckoning sultrily toward the audience and shooting at the camera\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popcrush.com/red-velvet-bad-boy-music-video/ |first=Annie |last=Martin |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=PopCrush|date=January 30, 2018|title=Red Velvet Releases New Album, 'Bad Boy' Music Video}}</ref><ref name=BillboardBB>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8096961/red-velvet-bad-boy |first=Tamar |last=Herman |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Billboard|date=January 30, 2018|title=Red Velvet Drops Perfectly R&B-Laced 'Bad Boy'}}</ref>\n\nOn January 29, 2018, Red Velvet held a [[Comeback (K-pop)|comeback showcase]] broadcast live through the [[Naver (search engine)|Naver]] app ''[[V Live (website)|V Live]]'' which was hosted by label mate [[Girls' Generation]] member [[Hyoyeon]] where the members discussed \"Bad Boy\" and performed it live for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=937504 |first=Won |last=Jeon |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=X Sports News|date=January 29, 2018 |script-title=ko:[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, \uc624\ub298(29\uc77c) '\ubc30\ub4dc\ubcf4\uc774' \uacf5\uac1c\ubd80\ud130 V\ub77c\uc774\ube0c\uae4c\uc9c0 |language=korean}}</ref> Red Velvet began their [[Music programs of South Korea|music show promotions]] for the song through ''[[M! Countdown]]'' on February 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1414327 |first=Jeong-min |last=Choi |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=10asia|date=February 1, 2018 |script-title=ko:\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3\uc774 \uc628\ub2e4\u2026 \uc624\ub298(1\uc77c) '\uc5e0\uce74'\uc11c \uc2e0\uace1 'Bad Boy' \ucd5c\ucd08 \uacf5\uac1c |language=korean}}</ref> The group also performed the song on ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]'', ''[[Show! Music Core]]'', ''[[Inkigayo]]'' and ''[[Show Champion]]'' where they achieved their first [[Music programs of South Korea#Chart systems|music show win]] for \"Bad Boy\" on February 7.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3230162 |first=Soo-min |last=Jang|accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=News1|date=February 7, 2018 |script-title=ko:'\uc1fc\ucc54\ud53c\uc5b8' \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 'BAD BOY' \ucc54\ud53c\uc5b8 \uc1a1 \ub4f1\uadf9 '\ucef4\ubc31 \ud6c4 \uccab 1\uc704' |language=korean}}</ref> The group received 5 total music show wins for the song.\n\nOn April 1, 2018, Red Velvet performed the song along with \"[[Red Flavor]]\" in [[Pyongyang]] at the [[East Pyongyang Grand Theatre]] to an audience that included [[Kim Jong-un]] during a concert billed as \"[[Spring is Coming]]\", intended as part of a wider diplomatic initiative between South Korea and North Korea. This made them only the fifth idol group to ever perform in North Korea and the first artist from SM Entertainment in fifteen years since [[Shinhwa]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2018/04/02/kim-jong-un-applauds-k-pop-stars-in-newest-sign-of-diplomatic-warming/|title=Kim Jong Un applauds South Korean pop stars in newest sign of diplomatic warming|last=Noack|first=Rick|date=April 2, 2018|work=Washington Post|access-date=December 19, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.sky.com/story/kim-jong-un-claps-along-to-k-pop-at-north-korea-concert-11312998|title=Kim Jong Un 'claps along to K-pop' at North Korea concert|work=Sky News|access-date=December 19, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=001&aid=0009982589|title=\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, \ud3c9\uc591\uc11c '\ube68\uac04\ub9db' '\ubc30\ub4dc \ubcf4\uc774' \ubd80\ub978\ub2e4|date=March 26, 2018|accessdate=December 19, 2018|language=ko|publisher=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The group also performed a half-Korean, half-English version of the song at a fan meeting in [[Chicago]] in April 2018, months before the release of its official English version in August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fuse.tv/2018/06/red-velvet-kcon-2018-ny-interview-bad-boy-english-version |first=Jeff |last=Benjamin |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Fuse |date=June 29, 2018|title=RED VELVET BREAK DOWN CREATING AN ENGLISH VERSION OF 'BAD BOY,' MUSICAL ASPIRATIONS AT KCON 2018 NY}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\nTamar Herman of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' labelled the song their \"darkest yet\", noting the difference between the rainbow hues of their last single \"[[Peek-a-Boo (Red Velvet song)|Peek-a-Boo]]\" and stated that the members \"played up their smoother retro leanings\" with the addition of the new songs in its parent album ''The Perfect Red Velvet''. Herman also commented on the song's choreography, which was seen as the sexiest the group has ever done. She then called the song and the album \"overall representatives\" of the group's \"velvet\" side (a reference to the group's [[Red Velvet (group)#Artistry|dual concept]]), which contrasted the quirkier \"red\" songs that the group has released in the previous year.<ref name=BillboardBB /> Avery Thompson of ''[[Hollywood Life]]'' stated that the song was \"music perfection\" and called the members \"the epitome of girl power\" in the music video. She also praised its choreography and the group's vocals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2018/01/29/red-velvet-bad-boy-music-video/ |first=Avery |last=Thompson |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Hollywood Life|date=January 29, 2018|title=Red Velvet Drops Perfectly R&B-Laced 'Bad Boy'}}</ref> [[Fuse (magazine)|''Fuse'']]'s Jeff Benjamin felt that the group put their own spin on modern R&B and hip hop and compared it to other artists such as [[Rihanna]], [[Tinashe]], and [[Cardi B]] who have incorporated \"sassy, catch phrases into their verses and choruses\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fuse.tv/2018/01/red-velvet-bad-boy-mv-perfect-album |first=Jeff |last=Benjamin |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Fuse|date=January 31, 2018|title=Red Velvet Are R&B Princesses for a 'Bad Boy': Watch}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'' opined that [[The Stereotypes]]' work on the album \"have helped hone the girl group's lush contemporary R&B-meets-pop sound\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tamarherman/2018/01/31/from-k-pop-to-bruno-mars-the-stereotypes-are-shaping-the-global-sound-of-music/#2149e72d569a |first=Tamar |last=Herman |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Forbes|date=January 31, 2018|title=From K-Pop To Bruno Mars, The Stereotypes Are Shaping The Global Sound Of Music}}</ref>\n\nIn the group's native country South Korea, ''X Sports News'' described \"Bad Boy\" as the perfect blend of the group's intense \"red\" side and soft \"velvet\" in their review of Red Velvet's dual concept \"red\" and velvet\" since Red Velvet's debut with \"Happiness\" and \"Be Natural\" in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=938340 |first=Ji-hyun |last=Lee |accessdate=January 30, 2018 |website=Sports Chosun|date=December 19, 2018 |script-title=ko:[\uc5d1's \ucd08\uc810] \ub808\ub4dc\uc640 \ubca8\ubcb3\uc758 \uc644\ubcbd\ud55c \uc870\ud654, 'bad boy'|trans-title=[X's Focus] The Perfect Harmony of Red and Velvet, 'Bad Boy' |language=korean}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2018, ''Billboard'' included \"Bad Boy\" in their '100 Best Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks' list while the song topped their annual '20 Best K-pop Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks' list, making Red Velvet the first female artist to top the list since it started in 2012. In the article, ''Billboard'' called it \"the group's and one of the year's most pristine production to date\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489483/best-songs-2018-staff-picks |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Billboard|date=December 11, 2018|title=Billboard's 100 Best Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8490486/best-k-pop-songs-2018-top-20 |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Billboard|date=December 17, 2018|title=The 20 Best K-pop Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |user=Jeff__Benjamin |author=Jeff Benjamin |number=1074792049566724097 |date=December 18, 2018 |title=History moment: For the first time since @Billboard began ranking the top K-pop songs of the year in 2012, Red Velvet is the first female act to be named for the year's best song. Congratulations, @RVsmtown, @Stereotypes, @SMTOWNGLOBAL and all involved!|accessdate=December 19, 2018 }}</ref> ''[[Dazed (magazine)|Dazed]]'' also included the song in their '20 best K-pop songs of 2018' and called the song \"understated but bold, a buttery, mid-tempo R&B track that puts the focus on the quintet's voices\" they then concluded that \"Red Velvet are already K-pop's most musically interesting girl group\" and the song \"solidifies them as one of the best in the game overall\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/42620/1/best-k-pop-songs-2018 |accessdate=December 19, 2018 |website=Dazed |date=December 17, 2018|title=The 20 best K-pop songs of 2018}}</ref> The song was also featured in ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'''s 'Top 20 K-Pop Songs of 2018' at number two, stating that \"In a year marked by terrible men (still) hogging way too many of the headlines, a girl group flipping the script and delivering an ode to stringing along a 'Bad Boy' makes it all the more perfect as one of the year's best releases\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.papermag.com/papers-top-20-k-pop-songs-of-2018-2624051281.html |accessdate=December 22, 2018 |website=Paper Magazine |date=December 21, 2018|title=PAPER's Top 20 K-Pop Songs of 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, ''Billboard'' once again featured \"Bad Boy\" in their decennial 'The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s: Staff List', placing 27th. Writing in the article, L. Singh called \"Bad Boy\" the \"perfect representation of their mature 'velvet' persona\", and further praised its composition, commenting on \"how tactile the sonic and visual layering of the song is\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8544710/best-k-pop-songs-2010s-top-100|title=The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s: Staff List|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+Year-end lists\n!Critic/Publication\n!List\n!Rank\n!{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''\n|rowspan=\"1\"|Billboard's 100 Best Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks\n|43\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489483/best-songs-2018-staff-picks|title=Billboard's 100 Best Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=December 11, 2018|accessdate=December 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|The 20 Best K-pop Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks\n|1\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=The 20 Best K-pop Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8490486/best-k-pop-songs-2018-top-20 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=December 30, 2018 |date=December 17, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Korea Portal''\n|rowspan=\"1\"|Top 10 K-Pop Songs Of 2018\n|2\n|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rapir |first1=Jessica |title=Top 10 K-Pop Songs Of 2018: BTS's 'Fake Love,' Red Velvet's 'Bad Boy,' iKON's 'Love Scenario,' BLACKPINK's 'Ddu-Du Ddu-Du' & More |url=http://en.koreaportal.com/articles/46460/20181221/top-10-k-pop-songs-of-2018-btss-fake-love-red-velvets-bad-boy-ikons-love-scenario-blackpinks-ddu-du-ddu-du-more.htm |website=Korea Portal |accessdate=December 30, 2018 |date=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Paper (magazine)|PAPER]]''\n|rowspan=\"1\"|P