n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |''[[Reddit|Reddit K-Pop]]''\n|Song of the Year 2018\n|1\n| rowspan=\"6\" |<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/kpop/wiki/annualkpopawards/2018|title=annualkpopawards/2018 - kpop|website=reddit|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n|-\n|Music Video of the Year 2018\n|2\n|-\n|Best Teaser 2018\n|1\n|-\n|Best Live Performance 2018\n|3\n|-\n|Best Choreography 2018 - Female Duo/Group\n|1\n|-\n|Best R&B Song 2018\n|1\n|-\n|''[[Dazed]]''\n|The 20 best K-pop songs of 2018\n|4\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/42620/1/best-k-pop-songs-2018|title=The 20 best K-pop songs of 2018|last=Dazed|date=2018-12-17|website=Dazed|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[BuzzFeed|Buzzfeed]]''\n|30 Songs That Helped Define K-Pop In 2018\n|1\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/sarahhan/best-k-pop-songs-of-2018|title=30 Songs That Helped Define K-Pop In 2018|last=Han|first=Sarah|website=BuzzFeed|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Tone Glow''\n|The 50 Best Korean Songs of 2018\n|1\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.toneglow.net/features/50-best-korean-songs-2018/2|title=The 50 Best Korean Songs of 2018|website=Tone Glow|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Decade-end lists\n!Critic/Publication\n!List\n!Rank\n!{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |[[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']]\n| align=\"center\" |The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s\n| align=\"center\" |27\n| align=\"center\" |<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8544710/best-k-pop-songs-2010s-top-100|title=The 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s|date=November 25, 2019|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 13, 2019|publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |''KultScene''\n| align=\"center\" |The 100 best K-pop songs of the 2010s\n| align=\"center\" |15\n| align=\"center\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kultscene.com/the-100-best-k-pop-songs-of-the-2010s/|title=The 100 best K-pop songs of the 2010s {{!}} Best Kpop songs of the decade|last=KultScene|date=2019-12-22|website=KultScene|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |[[Reddit|''Reddit K-Pop'']]\n| align=\"center\" |Song of the Decade\n| align=\"center\" |3\n| align=\"center\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/kpop/wiki/annualkpopawards/firstdecadeawards|title=annualkpopawards/firstdecadeawards - kpop|website=reddit|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Commercial performance ==\n\"Bad Boy\" charted at number one on Gaon's Weekly Download Chart and at number two on the [[Gaon Digital Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2018/02/08/2018020801013.html|title=\ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 \uc815\uaddc 2\uc9d1 \ub9ac\ud328\ud0a4\uc9c0, \uac00\uc628 \ucc28\ud2b8 2\uad00\uc655 '\ub300\uc138 \ud30c\uc6cc'|website=Chosun|last=Kim|first=Seong-won|date=February 8, 2018|accessdate=February 8, 2018|language=Korean}}</ref> Elsewhere, it peaked at number two on ''Billboard's'' [[World Digital Songs]] chart, earning them their best US sales to date, selling 4,000 downloads from January 26 to February 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8098865/red-velvet-bad-boy-best-song-sales-week-world-digital-songs-chart|title=Red Velvet Earn Their Best Song Sales Week in the U.S. Yet With 'Bad Boy'|website=Billboard|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=February 8, 2018|accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> \"Bad Boy\" also marks the group's debut on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] at number 87, becoming only the seventh K-pop artist and the third female act to appear on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8099605/red-velvet-bad-boy-canadian-hot-100-chart-debut|title=Red Velvet Debut on the Canadian Hot 100|website=Billboard|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=February 13, 2018|accessdate=February 16, 2018}}</ref> The song also charted in [[Japan]], [[Malaysia]] and [[Singapore]]. Moreover, \"Bad Boy\" has sold over 500,000 units in the United States, which makes it eligible for a Gold certification by the [[RIAA]].\n\nIn October 2019, the song reached 100 million streams on Spotify, making Red Velvet the first artist from SM Entertainment to reach this milestone. In April 2020, \"Bad Boy\" was certified Platinum by the [[Gaon Music Chart|Korea Music Content Association]] (KMCA) for selling over 2,500,000 downloads, marking their third song to reach the milestone, following [[Red Flavor]] and [[Russian Roulette (Red Velvet song)|Russian Roulette]], but the group's first to receive a KCMA certificate following the introduction of certicate system in 2018.<ref name=\"downloadcert\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/certification/list.gaon?serviceGbn=S1020|title=DOWNLOAD \uac00\uc628 \uc778\uc99d|website=Gaon Music Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Association|language=ko|trans-title=Download Gaon Certification|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref> \n\n==Credits==\nCredits adapted from ''The Perfect Red Velvet'' liner notes<ref>{{cite AV media notes| title=[[The Perfect Red Velvet]]| others=[[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]| publisher=[[S.M. Entertainment]]| language=ko| year=2018| type=booklet}}</ref>\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[SM Entertainment]] Co., Ltd.{{spaced ndash}}executive producer\n* [[Lee Soo-man]]{{spaced ndash}}producer\n* Maxx Song{{spaced ndash}}vocal director, digital editing, technician\n* Jang Woo-young (Doobdoob Studio){{spaced ndash}}digital editing\n* Gu Jong-pil (S.M. Yellow Tail Studio){{spaced ndash}}[[mixing engineer]]\n* Eazy $ign - [[mastering engineer]] \n* Lee Ji-hong (S.M. Lvyin Studio){{spaced ndash}}[[recording engineer]]\n* [[Yoo Young-jin]]{{spaced ndash}}lyricist\n* [[The Stereotypes]]{{spaced ndash}}composer, arrangement\n* Maxx Song{{spaced ndash}}composer\n* Whitney Phillips{{spaced ndash}}composer\n* [[Re